Hmmm, if I get this right the actual data connection also protected by GSSAPI:
```
    conn->recv[SECONDARYSOCKET] = sec_recv;
    conn->send[SECONDARYSOCKET] = sec_send;
```
If so then this issue could be considered more severe.

If that's the case, then we can avoid getting the "599 " into the data. Remember that it only stores that number if the block is actually 4 bytes or larger, so if the attacker injects an error using a smaller packet, it might be be possible to make transparent:
~~~c
    if(len >= 4)
      strcpy(buf, "599 ");

